  <!-- Risk Management -->
  <div class="fio-card">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">Risk Management Plan (Read This Twice)</h2>

    <div class="fio-grid2">
      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Objectives</h3>
        <ul class="fio-list">
          <li>Preserve capital while allowing for growth potential.</li>
          <li>Limit drawdowns so your account can survive normal losing streaks.</li>
          <li>Stay disciplined by following the rules (no “revenge trades”).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Position Sizing (Simple Rule)</h3>
        <p class="fio-p">
          Risk per trade should be a small slice of your account. Your original range was <strong>2%–10%</strong>.
          For most members, a safer default is:
        </p>
        <ul class="fio-list">
          <li><strong>Beginner:</strong> 2%–3% risk per trade</li>
          <li><strong>Intermediate:</strong> 3%–5% risk per trade</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced:</strong> 5%+ only if you understand drawdowns and can handle them</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fio-p fio-note fio-muted">
          “Risk” here means the maximum you’re willing to lose on the spread (what you paid for it).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="fio-divider"></div>

    <div class="fio-grid2">
      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Stop-Loss Strategy</h3>
        <p class="fio-p">
          For this blueprint, assume the <strong>full debit paid</strong> can be lost. That’s why sizing stays small.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Portfolio Limits</h3>
        <ul class="fio-list">
          <li>Avoid putting all capital into one ticker.</li>
          <li>Focus on: <strong>SPY, QQQ, IWM, DIA</strong>.</li>
          <li>Suggested cap: <strong>no more than 5 active spreads</strong> at one time.</li>
          <li>Always track total open risk across trades.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="fio-divider"></div>

    <div class="fio-mini">
      <h3 class="fio-h3">Weekly Review (Thursday)</h3>
      <ul class="fio-list">
        <li>Review open trades each <strong>Thursday before market close</strong>.</li>
        <li>If a trade is underperforming, decide: close early vs. let it play out (based on the plan, not emotions).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

