      <p class="fio-p">
        Each Thursday, check the Telegram group and your email for the trade details.
        Target delivery time is around <strong>3:15 PM EST</strong> (about 45 minutes before market close).
      </p>

      <p class="fio-p"><strong>How the ticker is chosen:</strong></p>
      <ul class="fio-list">
        <li>Review the past 5 days of SPY, QQQ, IWM, and DIA.</li>
        <li>Identify the strongest performer.</li>
        <li>Build the trade on that ticker.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="fio-divider"></div>

    <div class="fio-mini">
      <h3 class="fio-h3">Step 3: The Thursday Rule</h3>
      <ol class="fio-list">
        <li>Set up your trades.</li>
        <li>Ignore whether the market is up or down that day.</li>
        <li>Remain consistent with the strategy.</li>
        <li>Place your profit-target order (see below).</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Trade Structure -->
  <div class="fio-card">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">Trade Structure</h2>
    <p class="fio-p">We <strong>always</strong> use a <strong>bull call spread</strong>:</p>
    <ul class="fio-list">
      <li>Buy a call at one strike, and sell a call at a higher strike (same expiration).</li>
      <li>Max profit happens if price finishes above both strikes at expiration.</li>
      <li>Max loss is limited to the <strong>debit paid</strong> to enter the spread.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="fio-divider"></div>

    <div class="fio-grid2">
      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Expiration Date</h3>
        <p class="fio-p">We select an expiration closest to <strong>~30 days out</strong> because it balances:</p>
        <ol class="fio-list">
          <li>Time for the market to move.</li>
          <li>Reasonable option pricing.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Strike Prices</h3>
        <ul class="fio-list">
          <li>Choose the <strong>closest spread above</strong> current price.</li>
          <li><strong>Example:</strong> If price is $99.99, choose $100 / $101</li>
          <li><strong>Buy to Open</strong> the $100 call</li>
          <li><strong>Sell to Open</strong> the $101 call</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Profit Target -->
  <div class="fio-card">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">Profit Target</h2>
    <p class="fio-p">
      A profit target helps you avoid active management and improves consistency.
      The blueprint uses a target of <strong>25% ROI</strong> on the cost of the spread.
    </p>

    <div class="fio-grid2">
      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">How It Works</h3>
        <ol class="fio-list">
          <li>Calculate a <strong>25% gain</strong> on what you paid.</li>
          <li>Place a <strong>GTC limit order</strong> to close the spread at that profit.</li>
          <li>Let it work until it hits or expires.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="fio-mini">
        <h3 class="fio-h3">Example</h3>
        <ul class="fio-list">
          <li><strong>Cost (debit) to open:</strong> $0.59</li>
          <li><strong>25% gain:</strong> $0.59 × 0.25 = $0.1475</li>
          <li><strong>Target profit value:</strong> $0.59 + $0.1475 ≈ <strong>$0.74</strong></li>
          <li><strong>How to set the order:</strong> place a <strong>GTC limit</strong> to <strong>sell to close</strong> the spread at <strong>$0.74</strong> (platform wording may vary)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="fio-p fio-note fio-muted">
          Important: bull call spreads are typically opened for a <strong>debit</strong>. Taking profit usually means closing for a <strong>higher debit value</strong> than you paid.
          If your broker uses different wording, ask in the community and include a screenshot.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Summary -->
  <div class="fio-card">
    <h2 class="fio-h2">Summary of Steps</h2>
    <ol class="fio-list">
      <li>Get the trade details from Telegram.</li>
      <li>On Thursday, open your trading platform.</li>
      <li>Set the trade with: bull call spread, ~30 DTE, closest strikes above price, and a GTC profit target.</li>
      <li>Repeat every Thursday with consistent sizing.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="fio-p"><strong>Goal:</strong> stack trades consistently and efficiently — without emotional decision-making.</p>
  </div>

